textBox.richText: Went up to Fraser after the big meal with my parents on thursday. Looked at the report between WP and copper...copper had more stuff open. Max decided he didn’t want to ski, and Mom was “iffy”, so they stayed back, whilst I drove down to copper. Did the pass rather than 9 through Kremmling; takes about 75 min with clear roads and limited traffic. They opened Windsong under the timberline, so I could bomb that run.
